dcterms:creator: E. N. Lorenz
dcterms:description: The Lorenz attractor is a well-studied example of chaotic behavior, governed by a coupled three-dimensional nonlinear ODE. The system contains two prominent arms of a strange attractor, and trajectories chaotically switch between the two arms.
dcterms:title: Lorenz Attractor

dcterms:creator: R. FitzHugh
dcterms:description: The FitzHugh-Nagumo model is a nonlinear ODE given by the coupled equations modeling the dynamics of two coupled neurons. It exhibits rare but high magnitude neuron spikes.
dcterms:title: FitzHugh-Nagumo Model

dcterms:creator: M. Finzi
K. A. Wang
A. G. Wilson
dcterms:description: The double pendulum is a classic example of a chaotic system produced by the dynamics of a rigid pendulum with two point masses under the influence of gravity, with trajectories having distinct energies.
dcterms:title: Double Pendulum
